I knew Stokely was going to be a rap in everybody.

1333
02:13:58,000 --> 02:14:01,000
So I started talking to him and they said,

1334
02:14:01,000 --> 02:14:04,000
yeah, we might be used this one.

1335
02:14:04,000 --> 02:14:07,000
We'll go for this one.

1336
02:14:07,000 --> 02:14:11,000
So then he turned me over to the Oakland people.

1337
02:14:11,000 --> 02:14:15,000
Well, when I went to the meeting,

1338
02:14:15,000 --> 02:14:19,000
I was in Oakland maybe for a couple of weeks or so.

1339
02:14:19,000 --> 02:14:24,000
And when I went to the meeting with the Panthers,

1340
02:14:24,000 --> 02:14:28,000
I was told, we're not going to deal with you.

1341
02:14:28,000 --> 02:14:30,000
One because you've been right around town

1342
02:14:30,000 --> 02:14:33,000
and a steel-grade Cadillac.

1343
02:14:33,000 --> 02:14:36,000
I said, well, that belongs to Kaiser Cement,

1344
02:14:36,000 --> 02:14:38,000
and well, you belong to them.

1345
02:14:38,000 --> 02:14:42,000
And I said, would you haven't even heard what I got to offer?

1346
02:14:42,000 --> 02:14:44,000
Well, we've heard a little bit of it.

1347
02:14:44,000 --> 02:14:46,000
I mean, we don't believe it.

1348
02:14:46,000 --> 02:14:48,000
I said, thank you.

1349
02:14:48,000 --> 02:14:51,000
I called Noelle and I said, hey, you ain't no deal.

1350
02:14:51,000 --> 02:14:55,000
You don't need to go through this bullshit.

1351
02:14:55,000 --> 02:15:00,000
So in the meantime, I met other people in town.

1352
02:15:00,000 --> 02:15:03,000
So I said, well, no, there may be a way out of this.

1353
02:15:03,000 --> 02:15:05,000
I've met some community folk.

1354
02:15:05,000 --> 02:15:09,000
Maybe we can switch it over and give it to the community folk.

1355
02:15:09,000 --> 02:15:13,000
So he said, well, see what you can do.

1356
02:15:13,000 --> 02:15:17,000
Timothy L. Jenkins,

1357
02:15:18,000 --> 02:15:24,000
who was an advisor to SNCC from the very beginning

1358
02:15:24,000 --> 02:15:26,000
and Tim comes out of Yale,

1359
02:15:26,000 --> 02:15:33,000
out of National Student Association.

1360
02:15:33,000 --> 02:15:42,000
Tim is always, I consider it to be the mouthpiece of SNCC.

1361
02:15:42,000 --> 02:15:46,000
So I called him mouthpiece and I said,

1362
02:15:46,000 --> 02:15:50,000
hey, man, didn't you introduce me to somebody

1363
02:15:50,000 --> 02:15:52,000
that you had a partner somewhere out here?

1364
02:15:52,000 --> 02:15:54,000
I'm out here in Oakland, California.

1365
02:15:54,000 --> 02:15:59,000
And he said, yeah, I got a man out there by the name of Don Warden.

1366
02:15:59,000 --> 02:16:04,000
I said, okay, then I told Tim what I was doing and he said, okay.

1367
02:16:04,000 --> 02:16:06,000
Look him up.

1368
02:16:06,000 --> 02:16:10,000
So I looked up Don Warden.

1369
02:16:10,000 --> 02:16:14,000
I got with Don Warden and then I met him as his love

1370
02:16:14,000 --> 02:16:19,000
who was in charge of Social Service Department of Oakland.

1371
02:16:19,000 --> 02:16:25,000
I met Mr. Dumbro who was a construction person.

1372
02:16:25,000 --> 02:16:32,000
I'm thinking the NAACP's person name was Wes.

1373
02:16:32,000 --> 02:16:33,000
I'm not sure about that.

1374
02:16:33,000 --> 02:16:38,000
But I formed a community group.

1375
02:16:38,000 --> 02:16:43,000
That community group got together with Kaiser.

1376
02:16:43,000 --> 02:16:47,000
Got the acquisition of the land.

1377
02:16:47,000 --> 02:16:54,000
The senior citizens I was sitting today called Wes Project Equal.

1378
02:16:54,000 --> 02:17:03,000
What was the title of motivation?

1379
02:17:03,000 --> 02:17:09,000
I think Lord will tell me that the Kaiser was trying to show

1380
02:17:09,000 --> 02:17:16,000
some level of calmness that could happen.

1381
02:17:16,000 --> 02:17:21,000
There would be a demonstration that other things could happen.

1382
02:17:21,000 --> 02:17:25,000
If housing was a problem, this is one way that you could do it.

1383
02:17:25,000 --> 02:17:31,000
And it was a way to show folks who had not been involved in acquisitions

1384
02:17:31,000 --> 02:17:36,000
and all of the processes of going about building houses

1385
02:17:36,000 --> 02:17:41,000
or getting into the business, they were willing to put up the money.

1386
02:17:41,000 --> 02:17:45,000
And this was from big Kaiser aluminum.

1387
02:17:45,000 --> 02:17:52,000
This was a subsidiary of Kaiser aluminum sitting there in Oakland.

1388
02:17:52,000 --> 02:17:56,000
And I guess this was part of their payback to Oakland.

1389
02:17:56,000 --> 02:18:01,000
So I stayed with this company for a little while longer.

1390
02:18:01,000 --> 02:18:05,000
They had several construction contracts with different cities

1391
02:18:05,000 --> 02:18:09,000
with the model cities kind of stuff.

1392
02:18:09,000 --> 02:18:13,000
And each time I would be called in to go talk to the black community

1393
02:18:13,000 --> 02:18:18,000
but I couldn't hear what was going on in the white community.

1394
02:18:18,000 --> 02:18:22,000
So finally in a meeting I said,

1395
02:18:22,000 --> 02:18:34,000
Why do I have to say, why can't I know what's going on in the white folks meeting?

1396
02:18:34,000 --> 02:18:39,000
When I only got to go to the black folks meeting and take back what y'all see

1397
02:18:39,000 --> 02:18:44,000
happened in the white folks meeting. Why ain't I there to understand what's going on?

1398
02:18:44,000 --> 02:18:51,000
Well, you don't need to understand what's going on and you fight.

1399
02:18:51,000 --> 02:18:54,000
Yeah, I'm really telling you.

1400
02:18:54,000 --> 02:18:58,000
So I'm out on the street again.

1401
02:18:58,000 --> 02:19:01,000
I'm married by this time.

1402
02:19:01,000 --> 02:19:10,000
I got married late 66, 67 so when I got last at four years.

1403
02:19:10,000 --> 02:19:17,000
I'm now having back pains.

1404
02:19:17,000 --> 02:19:24,000
I'm having real sharp, sharp back pains.

1405
02:19:24,000 --> 02:19:33,000
So I go to the doctor and the doctor tells me I'm having muscle spasms.

1406
02:19:33,000 --> 02:19:38,000
And he gives me these little yellow pills and he tells me I have to take,

1407
02:19:38,000 --> 02:19:46,000
take them three times a day and after I take them I have to sleep for two hours.

1408
02:19:47,000 --> 02:19:55,000
I left the doctor's office and stopped by my favorite drugist.

1409
02:19:55,000 --> 02:20:01,000
And back then in the days you could get a whole sharp back full of riefer for $10.

1410
02:20:01,000 --> 02:20:07,000
I got me some riefer and I went and got me a fifth of Jack Daniels.

1411
02:20:07,000 --> 02:20:13,000
I went home in that same chair that I have sitting in my bedroom now.

1412
02:20:14,000 --> 02:20:20,000
I sat in my chair, I sat the pills on my desk.

1413
02:20:20,000 --> 02:20:25,000
And I took me a shot of Jack Daniels, I rolled me a joint.

1414
02:20:25,000 --> 02:20:31,000
And I sat there and I was trying to figure out how I'm going to sleep for six hours.

1415
02:20:31,000 --> 02:20:33,000
Take care of family.

1416
02:20:33,000 --> 02:20:38,000
Well, I only had the wife at the time but how am I going to work and sleep six hours?

1417
02:20:38,000 --> 02:20:42,000
Well, the first conclusion I came to, that couldn't be done.

1418
02:20:43,000 --> 02:20:49,000
So then I started thinking about all of the things that was happening to me at the time.

1419
02:20:49,000 --> 02:20:58,000
I had just been out on a consultancy with a buddy and I was working what we called a fish tank.

1420
02:20:58,000 --> 02:21:05,000
We were working for this black consultant, this black architect that had a black and white staff

1421
02:21:05,000 --> 02:21:08,000
and he went to sensitize the staff.

1422
02:21:09,000 --> 02:21:14,000
So I had all of these people in the room that I knew something more than each one of them.

1423
02:21:14,000 --> 02:21:23,000
And I had to make them interact in order to get them to understand that this man wanted you to do his work

1424
02:21:23,000 --> 02:21:27,000
and to hell with whatever you might think of him and whatever you might think of him.

1425
02:21:27,000 --> 02:21:29,000
Just get the contracts done.

1426
02:21:29,000 --> 02:21:34,000
Well, afterwards my boys, my guys with Thomas and Reggie did a great job

1427
02:21:34,000 --> 02:21:41,000
but you almost blew the act because you smoked three packs of cigarettes in an hour.

1428
02:21:41,000 --> 02:21:48,000
So that thought kind of came to me and I lit up another joint.

1429
02:21:48,000 --> 02:21:55,000
And I said to myself, maybe cigarettes has got something to do with it.

1430
02:21:55,000 --> 02:21:59,000
So I decided the next day I was not going to smoke.

1431
02:21:59,000 --> 02:22:02,000
I was going to do everything I did.

1432
02:22:02,000 --> 02:22:05,000
Normally every day and I did went through the day.

1433
02:22:05,000 --> 02:22:10,000
I came home but wife was blowing smoke because she smoked at the time.

1434
02:22:10,000 --> 02:22:16,000
She was blowing smoke on my face and it's, so I talked to a buddy the second day.

1435
02:22:16,000 --> 02:22:20,000
And he told me, say you go three days baby, you got it made.

1436
02:22:20,000 --> 02:22:23,000
I went fishing the third day.

1437
02:22:23,000 --> 02:22:26,000
I ain't smoked since.

1438
02:22:26,000 --> 02:22:30,000
I was up to three to nothing.

1439
02:22:30,000 --> 02:22:34,000
I just stopped.

1440
02:22:34,000 --> 02:22:37,000
I continued to look at the next few days.

1441
02:22:37,000 --> 02:22:41,000
I continued to look at them pills and say they ain't over yet.

1442
02:22:41,000 --> 02:22:45,000
Then I thought about coffee.

1443
02:22:45,000 --> 02:22:48,000
I'd get out to be and put my feet on the floor.

1444
02:22:48,000 --> 02:22:50,000
I had to get a cup of coffee.

1445
02:22:50,000 --> 02:22:52,000
I could floor I could wash my teeth.

1446
02:22:52,000 --> 02:22:54,000
I could get a cup of coffee.

1447
02:22:54,000 --> 02:22:57,000
Before I sit down and have a cup of coffee, I had to have a cup of coffee.

1448
02:22:57,000 --> 02:23:00,000
I go to, I take the bus.

1449
02:23:00,000 --> 02:23:03,000
Before I could get on the bus, I'd have a cup of coffee.

1450
02:23:03,000 --> 02:23:06,000
Get off the bus, get on the train, have another cup of coffee.

1451
02:23:06,000 --> 02:23:12,000
Before I walk into office, have a cup of coffee, get to the office, have a cup of phone ring, got to have a cup of coffee.

1452
02:23:12,000 --> 02:23:14,000
Interview somebody, got to have a cup of coffee.

1453
02:23:14,000 --> 02:23:17,000
I'm like this here.

1454
02:23:17,000 --> 02:23:20,000
So I said, well.

1455
02:23:20,000 --> 02:23:23,000
Coffee is the other one.

1456
02:23:23,000 --> 02:23:28,000
So I got rid of coffee and started drinking tea and other kinds of things.

1457
02:23:28,000 --> 02:23:31,000
Feeling a little better now.

1458
02:23:31,000 --> 02:23:36,000
Now I'm working, but I'm working at something I do not like.

1459
02:23:36,000 --> 02:23:40,000
I do not like because I'm not free.

1460
02:23:40,000 --> 02:23:44,000
I'm caught up into taking care of family.

1461
02:23:44,000 --> 02:23:51,000
My daddy's always, my daddy taught me, my daddy got paid the whole family sat there and he dealt with the money.

1462
02:23:51,000 --> 02:23:54,000
He took care of family first.

1463
02:23:54,000 --> 02:23:57,000
Then he looked at his hand and said, work shoes.

1464
02:23:57,000 --> 02:24:01,000
And then whatever else he had to do, that's the way I felt.

1465
02:24:01,000 --> 02:24:05,000
I was in a position that, in that first, Austin thing.

1466
02:24:05,000 --> 02:24:08,000
I didn't even see my paycheck.

1467
02:24:08,000 --> 02:24:11,000
I went to the bank.

1468
02:24:11,000 --> 02:24:14,000
She had the bank account.

1469
02:24:14,000 --> 02:24:17,000
I was one of the expensive accounts.

1470
02:24:17,000 --> 02:24:21,000
I had no expense account to do anything I wanted to do.

1471
02:24:21,000 --> 02:24:25,000
So I didn't even see money.

1472
02:24:25,000 --> 02:24:29,000
Now there's little other little jobs that I'm doing there.

1473
02:24:29,000 --> 02:24:32,000
I see the money.

1474
02:24:32,000 --> 02:24:36,000
I mean, I'm doing shit that I just do not like.

1475
02:24:36,000 --> 02:24:39,000
So the job is a problem.

1476
02:24:39,000 --> 02:24:49,000
Well, the job of becoming a problem, the marriage is becoming a problem for all kinds of reasons.

1477
02:24:49,000 --> 02:24:56,000
So Bobby Yancy calls me.

1478
02:24:56,000 --> 02:25:03,000
Oh, I finally got, well, I hadn't gotten quite got rid of the other job yet, but I'm on my way.

1479
02:25:03,000 --> 02:25:10,000
I had rid of this job because this job is part of my misery.

1480
02:25:10,000 --> 02:25:12,000
No, no, no, no, no, no.

1481
02:25:12,000 --> 02:25:15,000
That was just a quick consultancy.

1482
02:25:15,000 --> 02:25:19,000
No, no, no, that was an outside job.

1483
02:25:19,000 --> 02:25:22,000
Now I've left Austin.

1484
02:25:22,000 --> 02:25:28,000
I'm working for, who am I working for?

1485
02:25:28,000 --> 02:25:31,000
I'm a Western University.

1486
02:25:31,000 --> 02:25:40,000
I'm doing one of them welfare programs where they got to teach people to read and write or else they get put off a welfare.

1487
02:25:40,000 --> 02:25:51,000
I got a school more or less that's running from kindergarten to high school with 35 year old women.

1488
02:25:51,000 --> 02:26:00,000
And derelict men and, oh, Lord, have mercy.

1489
02:26:00,000 --> 02:26:14,000
And young students who haven't got their life together and crashing out and it's just becoming, you know, I'm just not wanting all of this stuff.

1490
02:26:14,000 --> 02:26:21,000
I've been married to a psychiatric social worker too and I'm just used to doing my own hustle.

1491
02:26:21,000 --> 02:26:32,000
And one of the things that me and my wife had agreement on is that once she got her masters, then she would handle things as we'd talk about little babies until things get right.

1492
02:26:32,000 --> 02:26:35,000
Then you take care of things while I put mine together.

1493
02:26:35,000 --> 02:26:40,000
Well, of course, by the time it came round for me, go to school, do this.

1494
02:26:40,000 --> 02:26:45,000
Well, I didn't tell you what to do.

1495
02:26:45,000 --> 02:26:51,000
Do what you do and I'll do what I'll do and I'll guarantee you everything will work out well.

1496
02:26:51,000 --> 02:26:53,000
All of that's happening.

1497
02:26:54,000 --> 02:26:59,000
I'm getting this phone call from Bobby Nancy.

1498
02:26:59,000 --> 02:27:05,000
Bobby says, got a project in Memphis, Tennessee.

1499
02:27:05,000 --> 02:27:11,000
If you're free, come right away.

1500
02:27:12,000 --> 02:27:16,000
I had a dog. I made it home.

1501
02:27:16,000 --> 02:27:21,000
I walked through the door and there she was, my ex-wife.

1502
02:27:21,000 --> 02:27:28,000
And she says, I'm getting another apartment.

1503
02:27:28,000 --> 02:27:30,000
I'm leaving.

1504
02:27:30,000 --> 02:27:39,000
And what I said to her when we first met was, whenever you get tired of me and you don't hesitate to tell me that you're going to go.

1505
02:27:39,000 --> 02:27:42,000
That's the end, that's the end.

1506
02:27:42,000 --> 02:27:47,000
So when she said it, I said, no, hold still.

1507
02:27:47,000 --> 02:27:52,000
I said, I'm going away for maybe about six weeks.

1508
02:27:52,000 --> 02:27:56,000
And when I get back, then we talk or something or other.

1509
02:27:56,000 --> 02:28:01,000
And I, over the course of time, I already packed some bags and stuff.

1510
02:28:01,000 --> 02:28:05,000
So I went on to this project.

1511
02:28:05,000 --> 02:28:22,000
The project was one of the first black caucus dinners in Memphis, Tennessee working for A.L. A.L. Nellum & Associates & Associates.

1512
02:28:22,000 --> 02:28:34,000
So we did that project and we came on back and Bobby gave me the option to meet her in DC because she was getting ready to take over a whole project here.

1513
02:28:34,000 --> 02:28:42,000
So I came back to Boston and things ain't what they used to be and ain't what they were.

1514
02:28:42,000 --> 02:28:52,000
I said, all of that stuff I got packed in the corner in my records and my chair.

1515
02:28:52,000 --> 02:28:58,000
And my chair, sitting at the address, I'll send you in.

1516
02:28:58,000 --> 02:29:05,000
I left Boston and I've been back here in DC since 81.

1517
02:29:05,000 --> 02:29:12,000
What's some of you think so many people have come to DC but maybe they're home?

1518
02:29:12,000 --> 02:29:18,000
Well, you can make a living here.

1519
02:29:18,000 --> 02:29:27,000
And then with so many of us here, we could get together and help each other.

1520
02:29:27,000 --> 02:29:47,000
One of the things that happened to me, even after I, after Bobby took the position with A.L. Nellum & Associates, it wasn't a solid kind of thing to do because he wasn't prepared to do the kinds of operations that was necessary to do the kinds of fundraising that was necessary.

1521
02:29:47,000 --> 02:30:10,000
So the project just kind of fell apart and then there I was out there again but because of who I knew around town, I could get other consultancies and little things to survive and then friends would loan me money to pay rent if I couldn't find the rent.

1522
02:30:10,000 --> 02:30:20,000
And then I got involved in the charter along with John A. Wilson.

1523
02:30:20,000 --> 02:30:38,000
I met and made friends that way and I was involved with a computer company called Afro-American Data Namix,

1524
02:30:38,000 --> 02:30:56,000
which was at 14th and Kenyan and it had the only computer on the ground outside of any black institution between here in New York and it was a DEC PDP-11/45.

1525
02:30:56,000 --> 02:31:01,000
It recovered its room.

1526
02:31:01,000 --> 02:31:09,000
And I was hooked up with a... got it right here.

1527
02:31:09,000 --> 02:31:18,000
So we did all kinds of activities such as what our main thing was doing polls and things.

1528
02:31:18,000 --> 02:31:29,000
And we did ((Marion) Barry) Barry, very first poll to the numbers and showed where he hooked everybody.

1529
02:31:29,000 --> 02:31:45,000
And of course showing him that and working things out after the election we were rewarded with a few contracts and things were going very well.

1530
02:31:45,000 --> 02:31:52,000
But back then, his days, electricity was bigger than what we could do.

1531
02:31:52,000 --> 02:32:01,000
We couldn't keep that big machine rolling and couldn't bring it enough contracts to keep it rolling so the lights went out.

1532
02:32:01,000 --> 02:32:12,000
So after that, I kind of went on unemployment for a few years, which was a good thing.

1533
02:32:12,000 --> 02:32:23,000
Then I was asked to come in and work with the youth division at what I worked for Pride before then.

1534
02:32:23,000 --> 02:32:29,000
But I was asked to come in and work with the youth division and the Department of Employment Services.

1535
02:32:29,000 --> 02:32:40,000
When (Marion) Barry was doing his first... well, it was the time he was doing his second summer youth program.

1536
02:32:40,000 --> 02:32:43,000
When we did the 40,000.

1537
02:32:43,000 --> 02:32:49,000
The first time was kind of a disaster because they hadn't done the checks and balances.

1538
02:32:49,000 --> 02:32:54,000
It was necessary to keep up and match up these kids.

1539
02:32:54,000 --> 02:33:01,000
So we matched up kids and kids went to the right places. They got their checks and it was a successful program.

1540
02:33:01,000 --> 02:33:10,000
And we did 40,000 one year in the summer and 25,000 in the school year.

1541
02:33:10,000 --> 02:33:15,000
I stayed with that program for about two, three years.

1542
02:33:15,000 --> 02:33:29,000
Then I went to work as an investigator for the Department of Employment Services in the Department of Employment, unemployment insurance.

1543
02:33:29,000 --> 02:33:36,000
And I busted quite a few.

1544
02:33:36,000 --> 02:33:46,000
And I sorted quite a few who was arrested.

1545
02:33:46,000 --> 02:33:52,000
And at that time the government was changing over from paper to data.

1546
02:33:52,000 --> 02:33:55,000
And I got involved in that.

1547
02:33:55,000 --> 02:34:02,000
And when I left the government, I was an assistant land administrator.

1548
02:34:02,000 --> 02:34:13,000
I was operating at least 100 machines managing and making that 100 machines.

1549
02:34:13,000 --> 02:34:24,000
I left the government 20 years to the day.

1550
02:34:24,000 --> 02:34:30,000
Only because I had planned to stay longer to help my partner.

1551
02:34:30,000 --> 02:34:38,000
Because I promised her I would help her until she got through to got all of the data in and straight.

1552
02:34:38,000 --> 02:34:41,000
