2023
03:13:08,000 --> 03:13:13,000
Yeah, I was with the child of the vote in Mississippi.

2024
03:13:13,000 --> 03:13:22,000
So do you have anything else to think about?

2025
03:13:22,000 --> 03:13:25,000
Yeah.

2026
03:13:25,000 --> 03:13:28,000
I can't help me out there.

2027
03:13:28,000 --> 03:13:32,000
I can't ask you anything else.

2028
03:13:32,000 --> 03:13:35,000
All right.

2029
03:13:35,000 --> 03:13:38,000
I can't unhide you with this.

2030
03:13:38,000 --> 03:13:43,000
What do you want people to know about the movement?

2031
03:13:43,000 --> 03:14:04,000
That we were lucky enough to have somebody like Ella Baker to present us with a very, very simple plan as taking people from where they are and bringing them up.

2032
03:14:05,000 --> 03:14:17,000
Those that are already on top don't necessarily need to push, but they need to support those from the bottom.

2033
03:14:17,000 --> 03:14:33,000
And those from the bottom would understand what the opportunities are for them and given the opportunity to look at that and examine that, then more people would move on their own and make decisions.

2034
03:14:34,000 --> 03:14:45,000
Based on their need, which would be, I think, I think that the majority of folks would begin to see that we all need the same thing.

2035
03:14:45,000 --> 03:14:51,000
And it would be easier to come together.

2036
03:14:51,000 --> 03:15:01,000
So I think that we left folks with us.

2037
03:15:01,000 --> 03:15:06,000
Something that I think that wasn't dealt with in any other movement.

2038
03:15:06,000 --> 03:15:13,000
We dealt with the thing that let folks know that they are the leaders.

2039
03:15:13,000 --> 03:15:17,000
But there's no one leader.

2040
03:15:17,000 --> 03:15:22,000
If you get up and you want to do something, somebody's going to follow you.

2041
03:15:22,000 --> 03:15:25,000
But you got to go and do what you want.

2042
03:15:25,000 --> 03:15:28,000
You got to know that you want to do something.

2043
03:15:28,000 --> 03:15:31,000
And you become a leader then.

2044
03:15:31,000 --> 03:15:37,000
And if enough people do that, then we have a movement.

2045
03:15:37,000 --> 03:15:42,000
We don't need another Martin Luther King.

2046
03:15:42,000 --> 03:15:55,000
And that was one of the things that we tried and still trying to get away from.

2047
03:15:55,000 --> 03:16:01,000
Even that movie that Oprah did.

2048
03:16:01,000 --> 03:16:18,000
I mean, she used a lot of money to tell a story that could have been told a totally different way and give up a lot of information that it would have been true instead of some factual, unfactual situation.

2049
03:16:18,000 --> 03:16:30,000
And compared that to the one that Robinson did called Freedom Song, where he depicted us going into Mississippi,

2050
03:16:30,000 --> 03:16:46,000
registering people to vote, getting the people involved as opposed to having Jim and John sitting in front of a conference with Jose reprimanding James Forman.

2051
03:16:46,000 --> 03:16:50,000
That has never happened.

2052
03:16:50,000 --> 03:16:53,000
Jim was not that kind of person.

2053
03:16:53,000 --> 03:16:55,000
Jim was as old as Martin.

2054
03:16:55,000 --> 03:17:02,000
Jim was as more of a leader than Martin.

2055
03:17:02,000 --> 03:17:18,000
And Jim had his own organization and was aware of the fact of having his own organization and having the strength of backing of his own people to say any damn thing he needed to say.

2056
03:17:18,000 --> 03:17:27,000
And at that point, we were already been chased out of Selma.

2057
03:17:27,000 --> 03:17:39,000
And he's already chased out of, I'm not Selma, but chased out of Southwest Georgia with them blastering in and not leaving anything.

2058
03:17:39,000 --> 03:17:40,000
Right.

2059
03:17:40,000 --> 03:17:45,000
Now what I'm talking about the movie, I'm talking about Oprah, right.

2060
03:17:45,000 --> 03:17:58,000
And then Oprah in a car, and then John in a car with Martin driving and Martin talking, that's bullshit.

2061
03:17:58,000 --> 03:18:03,000
Martin ain't drove no damn way.

2062
03:18:03,000 --> 03:18:08,000
And we didn't put John Lewis out.

2063
03:18:08,000 --> 03:18:12,000
It was John Lewis's choice to leave.

2064
03:18:12,000 --> 03:18:22,000
Always believed that he wanted to be an SCLC person anyway because he was brought up under that preacher, Jim Lawson,

2065
03:18:22,000 --> 03:18:31,000
loved that neighbor, Gandhi, whatever that stuff was.

2066
03:18:31,000 --> 03:18:34,000
I mean,

2067
03:18:34,000 --> 03:18:37,000
Were you at the meeting where I felt he was elected?

2068
03:18:37,000 --> 03:18:39,000
No, no, I wouldn't need either.

2069
03:18:39,000 --> 03:18:42,000
I wouldn't need either.

2070
03:18:42,000 --> 03:18:58,000
But Oprah could have used her money to do a different, if she wanted to do anything she should have shown the relationship that went on.

2071
03:18:58,000 --> 03:19:01,000
Because they were scared to death in Selma.

2072
03:19:01,000 --> 03:19:05,000
And they were scared to death in Albany, Georgia.

2073
03:19:05,000 --> 03:19:11,000
And each place they were telling us, don't do this. You all won't get killed.

2074
03:19:11,000 --> 03:19:20,000
The same thing that adult advisors was telling us everywhere, just stop.

2075
03:19:20,000 --> 03:19:23,000
So...

2076
03:19:23,000 --> 03:19:26,000
Yeah, it's not a very good depiction of the movie.

2077
03:19:26,000 --> 03:19:30,000
No, no, no.

2078
03:19:31,000 --> 03:19:33,000
Right. And they...

2079
03:19:33,000 --> 03:19:36,000
For some reason they want to...

2080
03:19:37,000 --> 03:19:41,000
They want to either rewrite the history or write us out.

2081
03:19:41,000 --> 03:19:48,000
And that's one of the things I think the value of the SNCC Legacy Project is.

2082
03:19:48,000 --> 03:19:58,000
Because it's coming back in a way that allows us to say and do what we know to do, which is organized.

2083
03:19:58,000 --> 03:20:05,000
I just got to email asking what to do, when to do, raising money and everything.

2084
03:20:05,000 --> 03:20:07,000
And I responded, I'm available.

2085
03:20:07,000 --> 03:20:09,000
Except for a couple of things.

2086
03:20:09,000 --> 03:20:13,000
I got to take piano lessons and recognize them dates.

2087
03:20:13,000 --> 03:20:15,000
And I'm trying to get some new needs.

2088
03:20:15,000 --> 03:20:17,000
So those are the only things.

2089
03:20:17,000 --> 03:20:19,000
Otherwise, I'm available to move.

2090
03:20:19,000 --> 03:20:26,000
If you want me to go down into Selma and go down into Ferguson to talk to some of them, I'll go.

2091
03:20:27,000 --> 03:20:35,000
And whatever you need me to do, if you don't conflict with my obligations, I'm free to go.

2092
03:20:35,000 --> 03:20:38,000
I still play the same role, if you need me.

2093
03:20:38,000 --> 03:20:42,000
If you need me, if you don't need me, leave me alone and I go fishing.

2094
03:20:42,000 --> 03:20:46,000
Which is something I love to do.

2095
03:20:46,000 --> 03:20:49,000
Any final thoughts?

2096
03:20:49,000 --> 03:20:52,000
Any minute?

2097
03:20:56,000 --> 03:21:25,000
I guess it's my dream to see a group of black folks come together in a financial kind of situation that's honest enough and got enough guts to not to be worried about consequences, but to be worried about a program and what's moving ahead and use our resources for what we know we can use them for.

2098
03:21:25,000 --> 03:21:32,000
And it's simple kinds of things that we can get involved in and help our community to grow.

2099
03:21:32,000 --> 03:21:46,000
Such as if we had a bank on the corner that could loan, that could loan, Miss Johnson, $25 to open up a laundromat,

2100
03:21:46,000 --> 03:21:55,000
loan, build Henry, $25 to open up a pool hall and that money comes back as some recreation.

2101
03:21:55,000 --> 03:21:59,000
Somebody else may want a restaurant.

2102
03:21:59,000 --> 03:22:08,000
Maybe we can talk one of these companies, one of these high tech companies are coming into a small town like Greenwood.

2103
03:22:08,000 --> 03:22:17,000
And Red Brown had a manufacturing company going on called Mace.

2104
03:22:17,000 --> 03:22:20,000
Where they made denim.

2105
03:22:20,000 --> 03:22:30,000
Why can't we find outlets and then let that money roll around in the community before it goes on.

2106
03:22:30,000 --> 03:22:34,000
Then it can go out on the stock exchange.

2107
03:22:34,000 --> 03:22:47,000
Henry G. Parks Jr, who I mentioned earlier on, they didn't find out that he owned Parks Sausage Co.

2108
03:22:47,000 --> 03:22:53,000
You know what Parks Sausage Co is? Parks Sausage Co is a sausage that's been out for years.

2109
03:22:53,000 --> 03:22:58,000
And it had a commercial called Bob Moses Mopalk sausage.

2110
03:22:58,000 --> 03:23:01,000
But it was a black, it was known as a black home business.

2111
03:23:01,000 --> 03:23:04,000
But everybody thought it was owned by Henry G. Parks Jr.

2112
03:23:04,000 --> 03:23:08,000
But it was actually owned by Henry G. Parks Jr.

2113
03:23:08,000 --> 03:23:14,000
And until it went on the stock exchange, nobody knew that it was owned by Henry G. Parks Jr.

2114
03:23:14,000 --> 03:23:26,000
But Henry G. Parks Jr was pushing money around in the community from a policy book.

2115
03:23:26,000 --> 03:23:41,000
Now if one man can have all of this business, he had businesses from Pikesville MD from Pikesville MD down to Pikesville MD.

2116
03:23:42,000 --> 03:23:49,000
He owned a Royal Theatre, which was all a part of the Chitlin' Circuit.

2117
03:23:49,000 --> 03:24:01,000
I'm saying if one man can take his finances, he sent his wife to the Victorine Q. Adams.

2118
03:24:01,000 --> 03:24:07,000
If one black man can put this kind of money together and do these kinds of things,

2119
03:24:07,000 --> 03:24:17,000
just think of maybe seven or eight putting in some money and going to work.

2120
03:24:17,000 --> 03:24:25,000
And when the clan walk up and say, you can't do this, fuck you.

2121
03:24:26,000 --> 03:24:28,000
We got enough to do it.

2122
03:24:28,000 --> 03:24:29,000
And I understand.

2123
03:24:29,000 --> 03:24:34,000
And somebody told me, says, well, Reg, once you build this kind of thing,

2124
03:24:34,000 --> 03:24:37,000
the bigger people will come in and buy it.

2125
03:24:37,000 --> 03:24:40,000
I said, well, then that makes it even better.

2126
03:24:40,000 --> 03:24:44,000
Because if we got something small here and the bigger people want to buy,

2127
03:24:44,000 --> 03:24:48,000
that means that more economics is coming down in here.

2128
03:24:48,000 --> 03:24:50,000
And that's where we want to see.

2129
03:24:50,000 --> 03:24:52,000
It want to see it grow.

2130
03:24:52,000 --> 03:24:55,000
So we don't want to see it to stop.

2131
03:24:55,000 --> 03:25:02,000
So if that can happen, I love to see that happen.

2132
03:25:02,000 --> 03:25:07,000
Somebody could say, you can talk to somebody.

2133
03:25:07,000 --> 03:25:10,000
You can say it works there.

2134
03:25:10,000 --> 03:25:15,000
That's it every day.

2135
03:25:15,000 --> 03:25:24,000
Well, I can't thank you enough for bringing to the Congress to have the chance to do these things.

2136
03:25:24,000 --> 03:25:30,000
Well, it all has something to do with me too.

2137
03:25:30,000 --> 03:25:36,000
USA Today just did a thing with me and I suppose we'll be coming out soon.

2138
03:25:36,000 --> 03:25:39,000
I was looking for that report and didn't find it.

2139
03:25:39,000 --> 03:25:44,000
And there's other kinds of questions that's coming up about me.

2140
03:25:44,000 --> 03:25:47,000
So and then,

2141
03:25:47,000 --> 03:25:51,000
legacy is trying to pull stuff together for us to do things.

2142
03:25:51,000 --> 03:25:55,000
So I figured it.

2143
03:25:55,000 --> 03:25:57,000
Right.

2144
03:25:57,000 --> 03:25:59,000
And for whatever reasons,

2145
03:25:59,000 --> 03:26:04,000
you know my policy of somebody coming up and asking me for an interview.

2146
03:26:04,000 --> 03:26:09,000
But if it's done in the context of what the legacy is doing,

2147
03:26:09,000 --> 03:26:13,000
then and you go to Charlie and Charlie proves it and everything.

2148
03:26:13,000 --> 03:26:19,000
That's cool with me, but still if anybody comes to me,

2149
03:26:19,000 --> 03:26:21,000
you know the policy.

2150
03:26:21,000 --> 03:26:24,000
This has been a presentation of the Library of Congress

2151
03:26:24,000 --> 03:26:30,000
and the Smithsonian National Museum of African American History and Culture.

